Description: GTK widget for GNOME canvas
DescDetail: <<
This is a straight port of the GNOME Cavnas from the
stable gnome-libs 1.2.4 back to gtk+.  The widget is
called GtkCanvas. This widget behaves identically to
the GnomeCanvas widget, with the same APIs,  except
the names are changed from gnome_canvas to gtk_canvas.
Thus you can use the GNOME documentation on this widget.
The test-gtkcanvas program in the %p/share/gtk-canvas/test 
directory can serve as a starting point on learning to use the widget.
<<
DescPackaging: <<
  The package also builds its own libart.  This is not installed, 
  but is used to compile the library that does get installed. It 
  does not seem to work with the existing fink libart, so this was
  the simplest workaround.  Static lib and header files moved to dev
  splitoff as of revision 25.
<<
DescUsage: <<
 The gtk-canvas package contains documentation and a test/demo program in
 %p/share/gtk-canvas/test 

 Only the static library libgtk-canvas.a  is supplied in gtk-canvas-dev.  
 To compile against it, you will also need to install the following packages:

   gtk+, glib, libiconv-dev, gettext-dev, x11-dev, imlib,
   gnome-libs-dev, libart2 (>= 2.3.16-2)
<<
